capstone.utility

Class Region

  • java.lang.Object
    • capstone.utility.AbstractPair<Point,Point>
      • capstone.utility.Region
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Region>

    public class Region
extends AbstractPair<Point,Point>
implements java.lang.Comparable<Region>
    Represents a region in a coordinate system. It is fully defined by a south-western and north-eastern point, but provides access to all four corners as well as other information about the region, e.g. it's area.

      • Region

        public Region(int width,
              int height)
        Constructs a Region with the given width and height, in the top left corner of the coordinate system, i.e. it is equivalent to a having the south-western point be at (0, height) and the north-eastern point at (width, 0).
        Parameters:
        width - The width of the region.
        height - The height of the region.

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Region other)
        Compares to Regions. Comparisons are performed by area.
        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Region>
        Parameters:
        other - The region to compare to.
        Returns:
        +1 if the area of this region is greater than that of the other region, -1 if it is less and 0 if it is exactly equal.
